OL,3,CConsumer confidence in economy falls
OL,4,Cto lowest point this year
OL,6,FHowever, because of a perception that
OL,7,Fthe UK economy is worsening, consumers
OL,8,Fsay they are reducing or deferring
OL,9,Fspending, the survey found.
OL,11,FOf those who agreed that the UK
OL,12,Feconomy was worsening, 56% said they
OL,13,Fwere cutting spending on everyday
OL,14,Fitems, up from 51% last quarter.
OL,16,FThe cost of groceries was the most
OL,17,Fcommon reason to feel that the economy
OL,18,Fwas worsening, at 81%, up from 79%
OL,19,Flast quarter, followed by the cost of
OL,20,Futilities, at 77%, up from 74% last
OL,21,Fquarter.
